article.headline: Evansville 100, Central Michigan 85
article.story: EVANSVILLE, Ind. (AP) -- Lucious Wagner scored 16 points, leading six Evansville players in double figures in a 100-85 victory over Central Michigan on Friday night. Andre Burton, Matt Webster and Dupree Fletcher added 15 points each, while Kyle Anslinger and Justin Petty had 11 apiece for the Purple Aces (1-0). The Chippewas (0-1) scored the first two baskets of the game, but the Aces tied it on two baskets by Burton and went ahead for the first time when Burton hit a free throw to complete a 3-point play. A layup by Wagner minutes later put Evansville in front for good. Burton had 14 of his 15 points in the first half, helping Evansville to a 53-34 lead at the break. The Aces, who scored 35 points off 22 Central Michigan turnovers, took their biggest lead at 61-34 early in the final period, and the Chippewas never came closer than 13 points the rest of the way. Kevin Nelson led Central with 24 points, while Giordan Watson added 16 points and nine assists -- and nine turnovers -- and Tony Bowne had 14 points.
